hat will unlock the ambiguous literary text. In examining the relation between obscene novels and sexual identity, The Novel and the Obscene instead illuminates the roles of both the novel and obscenity law in establishing sexual identity in American civic life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362532740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503625327423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503625327/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles